3ï¸âƒ£ WebSockets
Definition
WebSocket is a full-duplex, persistent communication protocol over a single TCP connection.

How it works

Initial HTTP handshake
Connection upgrades to WebSocket
Client and server can send messages anytime

Key idea
Real-time, two-way communication

Use cases
Chat applications
Live notifications
Online gaming
Stock price updates

Example
WhatsApp chat, live score updates.

